The development of spores makes POME microorganisms to be quiescent and highly resistant to lethal consequence of boiling, dry heating and ultra violet radiation from the sunlight (
 Okechalu 
  et al. 2011
 ). Palm oil mill wastewater is a possible habitat for lipolytic and cellulolytic bacteria and fungi since it is rich in nutrients such as lipids (oil) and cellulosic materials (
 Ohimain 
  et al. 2012a
 ; 
 2012b; 
 Bala 2016).
